********************ERPNext is an Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) suite that leverages the power and flexibility of open-source technologies.*******************

===>    Prerequisites:
      Ubuntu 18.04 server with at least 4 GB of RAM
      Python 3.6+
      Node.js 14
      Redis 5                                       (caching and real time updates)
      MariaDB 10.3.x / Postgres 9.5.x               (to run database driven apps)
      yarn 1.12+                                    (js dependency manager)
      pip 20+                                       (py dependency manager)
      wkhtmltopdf (version 0.12.5 with patched qt)  (for pdf generation)
      cron                                          (bench's scheduled jobs: automated certificate renewal, scheduled backups)
      NGINX                                         (proxying multitenant sites in production)
      
 1)   update server:
 
        $ sudo apt update
 
 2) Install Git:
 
        $ sudo apt-get install git
        
 3) Install Python:
 
        $ sudo apt-get install python-dev
        
 4) Install PIP (Python Install packages)
 
        $ sudo apt-get install python-setuptools python-pip
       
 5) Add the following lines to your /etc/environment file:

        $ sudo nano /etc/environment
        
      Now add the following content:
      
          LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8
          LC_CTYPE=en_US.UTF-8
          LANG=en_US.UTF-8
          
      ( press ctrl + x to save  then type y press enter to confirm)
 
 6) Reboot your server to apply all changes:
 
         $ sudo reboot
 7) Install virtualenv:
         
         $ sudo apt-get install virtualenv
         $ alias python=python3
         $ alias pip=pip3
         
 8) Install Maria DB Stabile Version:
 
       you can go through the given link for install various maria db version or follow the steps to install maria db stabile version 10.2 for ubandu 18.04
       
       https://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/repositories/#mirror=piconets
      
      $ sudo apt-get install software-properties-common
      $ sudo apt-key adv --fetch-keys 'https://mariadb.org/mariadb_release_signing_key.asc'
      $ sudo add-apt-repository 'deb [arch=amd64,arm64,ppc64el] https://mariadb.nethub.com.hk/repo/10.2/ubuntu bionic main'
      $ sudo apt update
      $ sudo apt install mariadb-server
 
 During this installation you'll be prompted to set the MySQL root password. else run the following command
     
     $ sudo mysql_secure_installation

9) installmaria db package:

     $ sudo apt-get install libmysqlclient-dev
     $ sudo service mysql restart
     
10) install Redis:
     
     $ sudo apt-get install redis-server

11) install Node.js 14.X package:
    
    $ sudo apt-get install curl
    $ curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_14.x | sudo -E bash -
    $ sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

12) install Yarn:
    $ sudo npm install -g yarn
    
13) install wkhtmltopdf:
    
    $ wget https://github.com/wkhtmltopdf/packaging/releases/download/0.12.6-1/wkhtmltox_0.12.6-1.bionic_amd64.deb
    $ sudo apt install ./wkhtmltox_0.12.6-1.bionic_amd64.deb
    $ rm wkhtmltox_0.12.6-1.bionic_amd64.deb

14) install frappe-bench:
    
    $ pip3 install frappe-bench
            or 
    $ pip install frappe-bench
        if you are geting pip install error use the following command
         
         $ pip install --upgrade pip
    restart your syatem or login again

 *********** Setting Up ERPNext 12*****************

15)  $ bench init [site-name]

16)  $ bench remove-app frappe  #this will remove default frappe app which was installed with bench

17)  $ bench get-app frappe https://github.com/frappe/frappe --branch version-13  #For frappe  if you have any repository and branch use your own instead of existing one

     


          
18)  $ bench start  # Run this command open new treminal and go through following command

19)  $ bench new-site [site name]
          while installing if you get any sql permission error:
            
            $ sudo mysql -uroot -p'your sql password' -Bse "GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'PASSWORD' WITH GRANT OPTION;"

20)  $ bench get-app erpnext https://github.com/frappe/erpnext --branch version-13 #For erpnext **read step (17)

21)  $ bench --site [site-name] install-app erpnext  # Install the erpnext app in site

22)  $ bench migrate  #make sure bench still running

23)  $ bench --site [site-name] set-config --global developer_mode 1

******************************************************************** END Thankyou ********************************************************************

